# SuperHabits — Cursor / Composer rules

## Primary architecture map

Before searching the repo for files, opening broad file trees, or proposing new paths, **read and use** `@docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE_MAP.md` as the source of truth for directory roles, import boundaries, sync/ID rules, and where logic belongs. Prefer it over ad-hoc exploration to save context.

If a requested change would violate `PROJECT_STRUCTURE_MAP.md` (or project invariants there: soft delete, migrations, sync enqueue, `createId`/`toDateKey`), **stop and ask the user for clarification or an explicit exception** instead of silently diverging.

## Module layering (strict)

- **Data** (`{feature}.data.ts`): SQLite via `getDatabase()`, `syncEngine.enqueue` after applicable writes, `lib/id`, `lib/time`. No UI.
- **Domain** (`{feature}.domain.ts`): Pure logic only — **no** `getDatabase`, **no** `expo-sqlite`, **no** `core/db`, **no** React. May use `lib/time`, `constants`, shared types.
- **UI** (`*Screen.tsx` and feature components): Orchestration and presentation only — call `.data` / `.domain`; **no** direct DB imports.

Never add DB imports to Domain files.

## Context hygiene

When work is scoped to **one feature** under `features/{name}/`, **do not read or modify files outside** `features/{name}/` unless the task requires it or the user **explicitly** references another path with `@` (e.g. `@core/db/client.ts`). Shared pieces: `core/ui`, `lib/`, `constants/` — only touch them when the change clearly needs them or the user `@`-mentions them.

## Naming conventions (new modules)

For every new feature module, use:

- `{feature}.data.ts` — data layer
- `{feature}.domain.ts` — domain layer (add Vitest tests in `tests/`)
- `{Feature}Screen.tsx` — main screen (PascalCase feature prefix)

Thin route: `app/(tabs)/{feature}.tsx` exports only the screen.

## Sync and IDs

After **every** mutating write on synced entities (per map: todos, habits, calorie_entries, workout_routines / routine bumps), ensure the code path calls **`syncEngine.enqueue`** immediately after the DB operation, matching existing `*.data.ts` patterns.

All new row IDs: **`createId(prefix)`** from `lib/id.ts` with the correct entity prefix from `PROJECT_STRUCTURE_MAP.md`. Date keys for YYYY-MM-DD: **`toDateKey()`** from `lib/time.ts` where applicable.

## Pre-edit confirmation (feature logic)

Before **modifying** a feature’s business or persistence behavior, **confirm in the reply** that you have read the relevant **`*.data.ts`** and/or **`*.domain.ts`** for that feature (and cite or summarize the touchpoints). If you have not read them yet, read them first, then edit.
